<subSubSection id="DA15A545F4BB0AD57E74FE9211A19032" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="6F82F69CFEAA482F5AC044654BD76E75" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B10B0D07A7E090CC3C35684F931376C8" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">
Worldwide, with approximately 810 species in about 45 genera. The tribe is underrepresented in the Northern Hemisphere with around 75 species (less than 10% of the world fauna). Only five species, all in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C77EF6C10113394858EF6C239DE9AB61" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Abacetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBD4AA1144FA7D7F37D9C0B44F9771DD" italics="true" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Abacetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are known from Europe and northern Africa. The Western Hemisphere is represented by about 235 species (29% of the world fauna) in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="AFD65E794B7A22FB51089987E0DC1AE5" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Adrimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45408AD9D848F2D4C5D025D297A38297" italics="true" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Adrimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates (22 Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName id="EF5EA882E8D0B972076CFD878C790688" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="793BE526A094E75CB0DC1CB1FF8902F7" italics="true" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Loxandrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(about 190 species), 
<taxonomicName id="EA55AC4CD436AFBDB72B9EEB7528CC4D" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Metoncidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="65467849F4C5BBB89E220C6CDFD323FC" italics="true" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Metoncidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates (one Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName id="37866A7CC2313B70C0D9A4DF0092212A" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oxycrepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8DA004857DF2693420130F0EE59A2903" italics="true" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Oxycrepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Reiche (four Neotropical species), and 
<taxonomicName id="445FA3286EC14CF6CCACAD087F6D49AE" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stolonis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7801369BB84E6FCDBB08EB553E073B8E" italics="true" pageId="486" pageNumber="487">Stolonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(19 species). All these genera belong to the loxandrine complex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8351C5FFC2B29810932C385CD6A9FC1B" pageId="486" pageNumber="487" type="taxonomic note">
